  "title": "KELLNER: Google to Launch Chrome OS in '09",
  "description": "Washington Times technology columnist Mark Kellner reports on Google's announcement that Chrome OS will ship in 2009 as a cloud-centric netbook operating system. Kastner \u2014 identified here as 'chief research officer at Scott-Page, a Westport, Mass., technology research firm' and 'a 40-year veteran of the technology industry and co-founder of the noted Aberdeen Group' \u2014 emails Kellner that web apps in the cloud usually work but are limited by network bandwidth and trust in the vendor's backup and security. Kastner cites a model flaw \u2014 'always-on Internet in emerging markets' \u2014 and notes consumers are using redundant cloud vendors (Picasa + Snapfish) to hedge against vendor failure. NEW career datapoint: Scott-Page affiliation 2009.",
